content.description: Up a left-slanting crack to a slopey rest spot, then up and over an interesting crux bulge.  Top out onto a big ledge, with easy scrambling up and over to the backside walkoff, or to access the tops of adjacent climbs.
content.location: Located about 15 ft to climber's right of Boo Boo Pumps You Up starting alcove.

content.description: A nice hand and finger crack

Ascend the bottom shallow crack (or diagonal up and across from the right) to get up to a short steep handcrack, then up a left-slanting wider crack to top out.  Rated 5.8+ in the JT West book, but felt like at least hard 5.10 to get to the one juggy side hold beneath that certain little plant.  Maybe stuff had broken off.  Lots of broken rocks on the ground.  Or maybe some mind-boggling trick to the start.
content.location: Located about 8 ft to climber's right of The Bear Necessities.

content.description:
Start approx 15 ft right of the center chimney, up the left side of the hollowed out alcove.  Follow parallel cracks to diagonal up and left passing a slightly overhanging portion to a midway ledge.  Fun pumpy moves.  Continue left to top out atop the right side of the center chimney.  Walk off by scrambling up and over to the backside and down.

Passed loose rocks that broke off.  Didn't seem like any previous ascent.  If not, happy to update to reflect.
content.protection: Single rack to 3" plus extra BD 0.75 and #1, gear anchor.
content.location: On the right side of the northeast face, just right of the center chimney, between Hiding From The Rangers and Scrabble Marathons.

content.description: a short, lousy climb with a loose start
content.protection: a few pieces of gear, if you trust them in loose rock
